<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[44955]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA['The Game of Love and Chance']]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Theatre.</strong> Josep Maria Flotats presents an adaptation of French playwright Pierre de Marivaux's best-known comedy at the TNC.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p><em>“El joc de l’amor i de l’atzar” </em> [The Game of Love and Chance] is the French playwright Pierre de Marivaux&#8217;s  best-known comedy. It tells the story of two young people who are betrothed in an arranged marriage. They both have the idea of pretending to be their servants, to secretly get to know the other person. Servants pretending to be their masters, masters pretending to be their servants and amorous misunderstandings lead to their secrets being revealed.</p>
<p>The play is full of elements that sought to break with the theatrical conventions of the period. When it opened in the 18th century, it was controversial because it was written in the purest tradition of French <em>comédie</em>.</p>
